<chapter xml:id="chap2-Rn-Space" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title><m>\R^n</m> as a Vector Space</title>
  
  <introduction>
      <p>
        In this chapter, we define <m>\R^n</m>, the <m>n</m>-dimensional Euclidean space as vector space over <m>\R</m>. We shall define abstract vector spaces in later chapter. In fact, <m>\R^n</m> can be thought of as model vector spaces and once we understand properties in <m>\R^n</m>, it will be easier to under properties in asbtract vector spaces. 
            
      </p>
